<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-09T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="492" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4363: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-09T17:00:00-05:00">November 9, 1933—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>446. The oppositionists who have surrendered at Atares amount to some
                                400. I am advised that the remainder who had gone there during the
                                night left the fortress before noon with their arms and proceeded
                                towards the south of the province.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>